track_notes:
Park on a pull-out along GC-216. We were first in the morning, but when we came back lots of cars were parking along the road. This is a very popular trail!

Follow the marked path. It gains some elevation in the first 20 minutes, then is almost flat and like a jogging path in the middle section. When approaching the summit it gets steeper again. 

There are two summits of about equal height. The first one is the one listed in the SOTA db, the second has a trig pilar. We took a roundtrip to the second one and then looped back to our original trail.

Alternative parking at Casa roja Casa de Tirma (28.03216,-15.68965). Adds about 1km of walking over other routes, but parking limited at shorter route.

Dont be fooled by the ascent on this one, theres nearly 600m of cumulative vertical ascent.
track_title: Alternative parking near Casa roja Casa de Tirma
